        <mxCell id="Lzv2f7MgehNdQIw8qka4-34" parent="1" style="shape=note2;boundedLbl=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;size=25;verticalAlign=top;align=center;" value="&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Partitioning principle:Highly regulated data (D1) must reside on on-prem or sovereign cloud; public cloud access only via controlled interfaces.Portability principle:Cloud-agnostic runtimes (e.g. Kubernetes, containers) for workloads that may move between providers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Security principle:Single identity and access model across clouds (federated IAM, central policies).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Network principle:All clouds are connected via a controlled hub-and-spoke model with central inspection.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Observability principle: Logs and metrics from all environments feed into a central observability platform.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Compliance principl: Multi-cloud designs must be traceable to data residency and sector regulatio&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="260" width="400" x="430" y="-740" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
